+*     UPSTREAM BUG FIX (vs ScaLAPACK 2.2.3): the post-loop condition
+*     was a copy-paste of the pre-loop condition above (line 416-417),
+*     so for SIDE/TRANS combinations (LEFT,NOTRAN) and (RIGHT,TRANS) —
+*     where the pre-loop is *not* supposed to fire — neither pre nor
+*     post fires, leaving the leftover block (the trailing partial-MB
+*     reflectors not covered by the main DO loop) unapplied. The
+*     correct post-loop condition is the complement of the pre-loop:
+*     `(LEFT .AND. NOTRAN) .OR. (.NOT.LEFT .AND. .NOT.NOTRAN)`, which
+*     mirrors SDORMRQ's structure (sdormrq.f:454: "(RIGHT .AND. TRAN)
+*     .OR. (LEFT .AND. NOTRAN)"). Documented in doc/UPSTREAM_BUGS.md.
